        <h2>Why the Hohmann transfer deserves more than a formula box</h2>
        <p>
          Orbital transfers are fundamental to spacecraft operations — from orbit raising and deployment to communication missions,
          constellation management, and interplanetary mission staging. The Hohmann transfer is often introduced early because of its elegance,
          but its deeper value lies in showing how an apparently simple result emerges from a very specific physical model.
        </p>
        <p>
          Studying this problem develops intuition about energy-efficient motion in a gravitational field, highlights the importance of assumptions,
          and shows how analytical equations become practical computational tools. In other words, it bridges theory, equations, code, and mission reasoning.
        </p>
